<dl id="sa0511z"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="sa" href="#sa0511z">SA (VI.A) </a>: <a href="../../ff/fnbs/ssaall.htm#sa0511z"> 511(z)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> phonetic theory is unsound:</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The paucity of Chinese sound could not so hold them. Neither is it conceivable that the whole list was made at once, as commercial codes of cipher are compiled. Therefore we must believe that <mark>the phonetic theory is in large part unsound</mark>. The metaphor once existed in many cases where we can not now trace it. <small> Ernest Fenollosa, &ldquo;The Chinese Written Character as a Medium for Poetry&rdquo;, in <a name="EFCW1" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EFCW1"><cite title="source">Instigations of Ezra Pound</cite></a> (1920) 385</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
